spanGrp.span: I think our weddings are celebrated in a very beautiful way.
bizım dügünnär nu bizım dügünnär bän zänederım güzäl oler
They invite everyone whoever is in the village to their weddings.
kank az halh onnar äp čağırierlär halh nädä nä var kövdä halh oturdi oturmadi gäldi getti
Lot of people are coming and leaving on their weddings.
öbür stol oturmamıš gälerlär onnar ötürerlär öbüri gider onnar gälierlär a tak eč
But it’s a normal wedding, I don’t know.
At our weddings tamada controls everything.
u nas bizım diah tamada upravlyaet vsyo
In their weddings everyone is tamada.
They put a lot of sweets on the table.
egıläri da onnar tökerlär mnoga pi šei pičyonnae čoğ sladki stol onnarın
They put everything on the table.
tökirlär emäh- to put a lot of food
Also they put a lot of national sweets and national dishes.
plyus natsionalnie sladosti čoğ birdä elä natsionalni blyuda u nih drugie est
